{
  "texts": [
    "1 In cooperative scenarios, Hernandez-Leal et al. [16] use learning communication to denote the area of learning communication protocols to promote the cooperation of agents.",
    "2 The only survey that we found classifying some early works in Comm-MADRL is from Gronauer and Diepold [17], which is based on distinguishing whether messages are received by all agents, a set of agents, or a network of agents.",
    "However, other aspects of Comm-MADRL, such as the type of messages and training paradigms, which are essential for communication and can help characterize existing communication protocols, are ignored.",
    "As a result, the reviewed papers in recent surveys regarding learning tasks with communication are rather limited and the proposed categorizations are too narrow to distinguish existing works in Comm-MADRL.",
    "On the other hand, there is a closely related research area, emergent language/communication, which also considers learning communication through various reinforcement learning techniques [18]."
  ]
}